se.cbb.jprime.topology

Class TimesMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • se.cbb.jprime.topology.DoubleMap
      • se.cbb.jprime.topology.TimesMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Sampleable, Dependent, RealParameter, StateParameter, GraphMap

    public class TimesMap
extends DoubleMap
    Specialisation of a DoubleMap to hold times of an ultrametric tree. Provides access to both absolute times of vertices and time span of arcs.
    Author:
    Joel Sj√∂strand.

        public TimesMap(java.lang.String name,
        double[] vt,
        double[] at)
        Constructor. Takes as input a list of absolute times (vertex times) and relative times (arc times). It is assumed that the times are in fact ultrametric and compatible.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the map.
        vt - the absolute times.
        at - the relative times.

      • getArcTime

        public double getArcTime(int x)
        Returns the relative time (arc time) of an arc, indexed by the arc's head x, i.e. time(p(x))-time(x). If x is the root, the "top time" is returned.
        Parameters:
        x - the arc's head.
        Returns:
        the arc time.

      • getVertexTimes

        public double[] getVertexTimes()
        Returns the actual vertex times of this map for low-level manipulation. User must ensure vertex times and arc times are ultrametric and compatible after changes to its elements. See also sister method getArcTimes().
        Returns:
        the internal vertex times.

        Returns:
